properties.headline: Winter Weather Advisory issued February 14 at 3:03PM CST until February 15 at 12:00AM CST by NWS Des Moines IA
properties.description:
...Blowing Snow Leading to Icy Roads This Afternoon and
Evening...

.Strong south winds have resulted in blowing snow across portions
of northern Iowa this afternoon. In additition to reduced
visibility, snow blowing over roads will cause ice to form. WOrse
conditions on west to east roadways.

* WHAT...Blowing snow. Winds gusting as high as 45 mph.

* WHERE...North central Iowa.

* WHEN...Until midnight CST tonight.

* IMPACTS...Patchy blowing snow will cause icy conditions on roads
and could reduce visibility at times. The hazardous conditions
could impact the evening commute.
properties.instruction:
Use caution while traveling, especially in open areas.

The latest road conditions for the state you are calling from can
be obtained by calling 5 1 1.

NWSheadline: WINTER WEATHER ADVISORY IN EFFECT UNTIL MIDNIGHT CST TONIGHT
